document_notes.text:
This update for curl fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2022-35252: Fixed a potential injection of control characters
  into cookies, which could be exploited by sister sites to cause a
  denial of service (bsc#1202593).

notes.text: When curl is used to retrieve and parse cookies from a HTTP(S) server, itaccepts cookies using control codes that when later are sent back to a HTTPserver might make the server return 400 responses. Effectively allowing a"sister site" to deny service to all siblings.
